{"parse":{"title":"Hindi-Urdu kinship terms","pageid":31088757,"revid":860683242,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Hindi-Urdu kinship terms</b> or <b>Hindustani kinship terms</b> describe every familial relationship. In the <a href=\"/wiki/Hindi-Urdu\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hindi-Urdu\">Hindi-Urdu</a> family tree various titles are used to represent one's <a href=\"/wiki/Family\" title=\"Family\">family</a> members. The Hindi-Urdu kinship system differs from the English one in certain respects.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In the Hindustani language, the kinship system is based on gender,<sup id=\"cite_ref-SouthworthDaswani1974_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SouthworthDaswani1974-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and some kinship terms are also used in order to give respect.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HansenMalmkj\u00e6r2004_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HansenMalmkj\u00e6r2004-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Moreover, \"In Hindi and Urdu kinship terms there is clear- out distinction between the blood relations and affinal relations.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Trivedi1983_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Trivedi1983-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Relations\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Relations</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Paternal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Paternal</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Maternal\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Maternal</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Siblings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Siblings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Brother&#39;s_family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Brother's family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Sister&#39;s_family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sister's family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Individual&#39;s_family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Individual's family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#In-Laws\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In-Laws</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Relations\">Relations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Relations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Paternal\">Paternal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Paternal\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Pardada\t(\u092a\u0930\u0926\u093e\u0926\u093e, \u067e\u0631\u062f\u0627\u062f\u0627)\t- One's father's father's Father (One's paternal great-grandfather)\n</p><p>Pardadi\t(\u092a\u0930\u0926\u093e\u0926\u0940, \u067e\u0631\u062f\u0627\u062f\u06cc)\t- One's father's father's Mother (One's paternal great-grandmother)\n</p><p>Dada (\u0926\u093e\u0926\u093e, \u062f\u0627\u062f\u0627)\t\t- One's father's father (One's paternal grandfather)\n</p><p>Dadi (\u0926\u093e\u0926\u0940, \u062f\u0627\u062f\u06cc)\t\t- One's father's mother (One's paternal grandmother)\n</p><p>Papa (\u092a\u093e\u092a\u093e, \u067e\u0627\u067e\u0627)\t\t- One's father\n</p><p>Pitaji (\u092a\u093f\u0924\u093e\u091c\u0940, \u067e\u062a\u0627\u062c\u06cc)\t- One's father (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Abba\t                - One's father (used mainly by the Muslim community)\n</p><p>Chacha (\u091a\u093e\u091a\u093e, \u0686\u0627\u0686\u0627)\t- One's father's younger brother\n</p><p>Chachi (\u091a\u093e\u091a\u0940, \u0686\u0627\u0686\u06cc)\t- One's father's younger brother's wife\n</p><p>Tau (\u0924\u093e\u090a, \u062a\u0627\u064f\u0651\u0648)   \t- One's father's elder brother \n</p><p>Taya (\u0924\u093e\u092f\u093e, \u062a\u0627\u06cc\u0627)        - One's father's elder brother \n</p><p>Barka Abba              - One's father's elder brother (used mainly by the Muslim community)\n</p><p>Bare Papa (\u092c\u0921\u093c\u0947 \u092a\u093e\u092a\u093e, \u0628\u0691\u06d2 \u067e\u0627\u067e\u0627) - One's father's elder brother\n</p><p>Tai \t                 - One's father's elder brother's wife\n</p><p>Bari Ma\t(\u092c\u0921\u093c\u0940 \u092e\u093e\u0901, \u0628\u0691\u06cc \u0645\u0627\u06ba)  - One's father's elder brother's wife\n</p><p>Bua (\u092c\u0941\u0906, \u0628\u0648\u0627)           - One's father's sister \n</p><p>Phuphi (\u092b\u0942\u092b\u0940, \u067e\u06be\u067e\u06cc)        - One's father's sister \n</p><p>Phupha (\u092b\u0942\u092b\u093e, \u067e\u06be\u0648\u067e\u0627)        - One's father's sister's husband\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Maternal\">Maternal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Maternal\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Parnana (\u092a\u0930\u0928\u093e\u0928\u093e, \u067e\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0646\u0627) \t- One's Mother's Father's Father\n</p><p>Parnani\t(\u092a\u0930\u0928\u093e\u0928\u0940, \u067e\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0646\u06cc) - One's Mother's Father's Mother\n</p><p>Nana (\u0928\u093e\u0928\u093e, \u0646\u0627\u0646\u0627)  \t        - One's Mother's father\n</p><p>Nani (\u0928\u093e\u0928\u0940, \u0646\u0627\u0646\u06cc)  \t        - One's Mother's Mother\n</p><p>Ma/Amma/Ammi (\u092e\u093e\u0901, \u0645\u0627\u06ba) \t         - One's mother\n</p><p>Mausi/Mausiya (\u092e\u094c\u0938\u0940,  \u0645\u0648\u0633\u06cc) \t        - One's mother's Sister (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Khala/Barki Amma                - One's mother's elder sister (used by the Muslim community)\n</p><p>Mausa (\u092e\u094c\u0938\u093e, \u0645\u0648\u0633\u0627) \t        - One's mother's Sister's husband (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Mama (\u092e\u093e\u092e\u093e, \u0645\u0627\u0645\u0627)\t        - One's mother's brother\n</p><p>Mami (\u092e\u093e\u092e\u0940, \u0645\u0627\u0645\u06cc)\t        - One's mother's brother's wife\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Siblings\">Siblings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Siblings\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Bhai (\u092d\u093e\u0908, \u0628\u06be\u0627\u0626\u06cc) / Bhaiya (\u092d\u0948\u092f\u093e, \u0628\u06be\u0626\u064a\u0627)   - One's parent's (share at least one parent) Son (your Brother, male sibling)<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Behen (\u092c\u0939\u0928, \u0628\u06c1\u06cc\u06ba) \t- One's parent's (share at least one parent) daughter (your younger Sister, female sibling)\n</p><p>Didi (\u0926\u0940\u0926\u0940, \u062f\u06cc\u062f\u06cc)\t- One's parent's (share at least one parent) daughter (your elder Sister, female sibling)\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Brother.27s_family\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Brother's_family\">Brother's family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Brother&#039;s family\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Bhabhi\" title=\"Bhabhi\">Bhabhi</a> (\u092d\u093e\u092c\u0940, \u0628\u06be\u0627\u0628\u06cc) - Brother's Wife (usually applied for an elder brother's wife)\n</p><p>Bhatija (\u092d\u0924\u0940\u091c\u093e,\u0628\u06be\u062a\u06cc\u062c\u0627) - One's Brother's Son\n</p><p>Bhatiji (\u092d\u0924\u0940\u091c\u0940, \u0628\u06be\u062a\u06cc\u062c\u06cc) - One's Brother's Daughter\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Sister.27s_family\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sister's_family\">Sister's family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Sister&#039;s family\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Jija (\u091c\u0940\u091c\u093e, \u062c\u06cc\u062c\u0627) - Sister's Husband (usually applied for an elder sister's husband)\n</p><p>Bhanja (\u092d\u093e\u0902\u091c\u093e, \u0628\u06be\u0627\u0646\u062c\u0627) - One's Sister's Son\n</p><p>Bhanji (\u092d\u093e\u0902\u091c\u0940, \u0628\u06be\u0627\u0646\u062c\u06cc) - One's Sister's Daughter\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Individual.27s_family\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Individual's_family\">Individual's family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Individual&#039;s family\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Main (\u092e\u0948\u0902, \u0645\u06cc\u06ba)\t- First form ('I')\n</p><p>Patni (\u092a\u0924\u094d\u0928\u0940, \t- One's wife<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Biwi (\u092c\u0940\u0935\u0940, \u0628\u06cc\u0648\u06cc)    - One's wife \n</p><p>Pati (\u092a\u0924\u0940, \u067e\u062a\u06cc)    - One's husband (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Khavind (\u0916\u093c\u093e\u0935\u093f\u0902\u0926, \u062e\u0627\u0648\u0646\u062f) - One's husband (used mainly by the Muslim community)\n</p><p>Beta (\u092c\u0947\u091f\u093e, \u0628\u06cc\u0679\u0627)\t- One's Son\n</p><p>Beti (\u092c\u0947\u091f\u0940, \u0628\u06cc\u0679\u06cc) \t- One's Daughter\n</p><p>Pota (\u092a\u094b\u0924\u093e, \u067e\u0648\u062a\u0627) - Son's Son\n</p><p>Poti (\u092a\u094b\u0924\u0940, \u067e\u0648\u062a\u06cc) - Son's Daughter\n</p><p>Naati (\u0928\u093e\u0924\u0940, \u0646\u0627\u062a\u06cc) - Daughter's Son (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Naatin (\u0928\u093e\u0924\u093f\u0928, \u0646\u0627\u062a\u0650\u0646) - Daughter's Daughter (used mainly by the Hindu community)\n</p><p>Nawaasa (\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0633\u06c1 \u0928\u0935\u093e\u0938\u093e) - Daughter's son (used mainly by the Muslim community)\n</p><p>Nawaasi (\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0633\u06cc \u0928\u0935\u093e\u0938\u0940) - Daughter's daughter (used mainly by the Muslim community)\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In-Laws\">In-Laws</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: In-Laws\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Sasur (\u0938\u0938\u0941\u0930, \u0633\u0633\u064f\u0631)  - One's Husband's/Wife's Father (Father-in-Law)\n</p><p>Sas (\u0938\u093e\u0938, \u0633\u0627\u0633) - One's Husband's/Wife's Mother (Mother-in-Law)\n</p><p>Damadh          - One's son-in-law\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint portal plainlist tright\" style=\"margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px\">\n<ul style=\"display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold\">\n<li style=\"display:table-row\"><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center\"><img alt=\"flag\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/32px-Flag_of_India.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"21\" class=\"noviewer thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/48px-Flag_of_India.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/64px-Flag_of_India.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1350\" data-file-height=\"900\" /></span><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle\"><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:India\" title=\"Portal:India\">India portal</a></span></li>\n<li style=\"display:table-row\"><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center\"><img alt=\"flag\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Flag_of_Pakistan.svg/32px-Flag_of_Pakistan.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"21\" class=\"noviewer thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Flag_of_Pakistan.svg/48px-Flag_of_Pakistan.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Flag_of_Pakistan.svg/64px-Flag_of_Pakistan.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"900\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></span><span style=\"display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle\"><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Pakistan\" title=\"Portal:Pakistan\">Pakistan portal</a></span></li></ul></div>\n<div class=\"div-col columns column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Hindustani_etymology\" title=\"Hindustani etymology\">Hindustani etymology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hindustani_grammar\" title=\"Hindustani grammar\">Hindustani grammar</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hindustani_orthography\" title=\"Hindustani orthography\">Hindustani orthography</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hindustani_phonology\" title=\"Hindustani phonology\">Hindustani phonology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hindi-Urdu_vocabulary\" title=\"Hindi-Urdu vocabulary\">Hindi-Urdu vocabulary</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hindi_and_Urdu_wedding_songs\" title=\"Hindi and Urdu wedding songs\">Hindi and Urdu wedding songs</a></li></ul>\n</div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Shapiro, Michael C.; Schiffman, Harold F. (1981). <i>Language and Society in South Asia</i>. Motilal Banarsidass Publishers. p.&#160;229. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9788120826076\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9788120826076\">9788120826076</a>. <q>Southworth and Dawsanigo on in their discussion of theoretical properties of kinship systems to show that while the English kinship system differs from both the Hindi-Urdu system and the Tamil one, the latter two systems also differ from each other.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Language+and+Society+in+South+Asia&amp;rft.pages=229&amp;rft.pub=Motilal+Banarsidass+Publishers&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.isbn=9788120826076&amp;rft.aulast=Shapiro&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael+C.&amp;rft.au=Schiffman%2C+Harold+F.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHindi-Urdu+kinship+terms\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SouthworthDaswani1974-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-SouthworthDaswani1974_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Southworth, Franklin C.; Daswani, Chander J. (1974). <i>Foundations of linguistics</i>. Free Press. p.&#160;190. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780029303009\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780029303009\">9780029303009</a>. <q>In this case, EGO can be of either sex (though in some kinship systems, such as that of Hindi-Urdu, the sex of EGO affects the choice of terms for certain relatives).</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Foundations+of+linguistics&amp;rft.pages=190&amp;rft.pub=Free+Press&amp;rft.date=1974&amp;rft.isbn=9780029303009&amp;rft.aulast=Southworth&amp;rft.aufirst=Franklin+C.&amp;rft.au=Daswani%2C+Chander+J.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHindi-Urdu+kinship+terms\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-HansenMalmkj\u00e6r2004-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-HansenMalmkj\u00e6r2004_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Hansen, Gyde; Malmkj\u00e6r, Kirsten; Gile, Daniel (1 January 2004). <i>Claims, Changes and Challenges in Translation Studies: Selected Contributions from the EST Congress, Copenhagen 2001</i>. John Benjamins Publishing. p.&#160;276. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789027216564\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9789027216564\">9789027216564</a>. <q>Kinship terms are also used for respect (e.g. 'older sister' for a woman one's own age or slightly older and the ubiquitous 'auntie' or 'uncle' in both Hindi/Urdu and English, especially but not exclusively used by children).</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Claims%2C+Changes+and+Challenges+in+Translation+Studies%3A+Selected+Contributions+from+the+EST+Congress%2C+Copenhagen+2001&amp;rft.pages=276&amp;rft.pub=John+Benjamins+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2004-01-01&amp;rft.isbn=9789027216564&amp;rft.aulast=Hansen&amp;rft.aufirst=Gyde&amp;rft.au=Malmkj%C3%A6r%2C+Kirsten&amp;rft.au=Gile%2C+Daniel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHindi-Urdu+kinship+terms\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Trivedi1983-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Trivedi1983_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Trivedi, Govind Mohan (1983). <i>Socio-linguistic study in an Andhra village</i>. Anthropological Survey of India, Govt. of India. p.&#160;89.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Socio-linguistic+study+in+an+Andhra+village&amp;rft.pages=89&amp;rft.pub=Anthropological+Survey+of+India%2C+Govt.+of+India&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft.aulast=Trivedi&amp;rft.aufirst=Govind+Mohan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHindi-Urdu+kinship+terms\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> <span style=\"display:none;font-size:100%\" class=\"error citation-comment\"><code style=\"color:inherit; border:inherit; padding:inherit;\">&#124;access-date=</code> requires <code style=\"color:inherit; border:inherit; padding:inherit;\">&#124;url=</code> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#accessdate_missing_url\" title=\"Help:CS1 errors\">help</a>)</span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.shabdkosh.com/s?e=brother&amp;f=0&amp;t=10&amp;l=hi\">Shabdosh brother</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.shabdkosh.com/s?e=wife&amp;f=0&amp;t=10&amp;l=hi\">[1]</a> Shabdosh wife</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hindi-Urdu_kinship_terms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n